Symptomatic Illnesses - EPI1 Scenarios

Pragati Prasad

2020-10-23

Mean, Cumulative with 95% CI, and Percent Averted

Scenario HP01

Base Scenario: R0 1.4 and “2009-like” severity

library(ggsci)
library(reshape)
library(dplyr)
library(gridExtra)
library(ggplot2)
library(egg)
library(plyr)
library(tidyr)
library(knitr)
library(kableExtra)


path <- "../model-forecasts/"

team.folder <- c("Columbia/COL/EPI1/", "Northeastern/EPI1/", "UTAustin/", "UVirginia/", "Imperial/", "Columbia/COL2/EPI1/")
team.abbrev <- c("COL", "NEU", "UTA", "UVA", "IMP", "COL2")
file.types <-c("SymIllness", "Hosp", "Deaths", "AntiviralTX")
scn = "HP01_"
read_overall_mean <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean", "sm.perc2p5", "sm.perc97p5")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[1],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  symillness <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:6){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("HP", "HP_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    f = paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[1],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[1],team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }
    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      symillness <- rbind.fill(symillness, 
                               data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  symillness$Cml[which(is.na(symillness$Cml))] <- symillness$cml[which(is.na(symillness$Cml))]
  cml <<- symillness[c("Cml", "team", "Bin")]
  
  long <- gather(symillness, week, illnesses, weeks, factor_key=TRUE)
  long$week <- as.integer(gsub("Week", "", long$week))
  
  cols <- c("Bin", "team", "week", "illnesses")
  long <- long[cols]
  long_wide <- spread(long, Bin, illnesses)
  
  return(long_wide)
}

long_HP01 <- read_overall_mean(scn = "HP01_")

ggplot(data = long_HP01, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("% Incident Symptomatic Illness") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cumulative % Ill` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:7], digits = 2, caption = "HP01, No Intervention", align=rep('c', 3)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

#Bar chart for age
team.folder <- c("Columbia/COL/EPI1/", "Northeastern/EPI1/", "UTAustin/", "UVirginia/", "Imperial/", "Columbia/COL2/EPI1/")
team.abbrev <- c("COL", "NEU", "UTA", "UVA", "IMP", "COL2")
file.types <-c("SymIllness", "Hosp", "Deaths", "AntiviralTX")
scn = "HP01_"
read_ages <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[1],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  symillness <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:6){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("HP", "HP_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    f = paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[1],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[1],team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }
    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      symillness <- rbind.fill(symillness, 
                               data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  symillness$Cml[which(is.na(symillness$Cml))] <- symillness$cml[which(is.na(symillness$Cml))]
  cml <- symillness[c("Cml", "team", "Bin", "Agegroup")]
  cml$Agegroup <- sub("yr", "years", cml$Agegroup)
  cml$Agegroup <- factor(x = cml$Agegroup, levels = c("0-4 years", "5-17 years", "18-49 years", "50-64 years", "65+ years"))
  cml$Cml <- cml$Cml / 100
  
  return(cml)
}

ages_1 <- read_ages(scn = "HP01_")
ggplot(ages_1, aes(fill=Agegroup, y=Cml, x=team)) + 
  geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
  ylab("Percent")+
  scale_fill_d3()

VX1

“Early”: Vaccine available 100 days after September 1

scenario <- "HP02_"

long <- read_overall_mean(scn = scenario)

ggplot(data = long, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("% Incident Symptomatic Illness") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cumulative % Ill` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Absolute Averted % Ill (HP01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cumulative % Ill` - table$`Cumulative % Ill`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cumulative % Ill` - table$`Cumulative % Ill`) / table1$`Cumulative % Ill`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "HP02: Compared to HP01", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

NEU 20.40 (19.83, 22.1) 7.14 25.93
UTA 16.89 (1.49, 31.37) 20.22 54.49
UVA 17.39 (7.76, 24.16) 4.96 22.20
IMP 0.00 (0, 0) 15.21 99.98
COL2 25.71 (23.33, 27.36) 1.35 5.00 
#Bar chart for ages
ages <- read_ages(scn = scenario)
ggplot(ages, aes(fill=Agegroup, y=Cml, x=team)) + 
  geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
  ylab("Percent")+
  scale_fill_d3()

averted <- data.frame(scenario = rep(scenario, nrow(table)),
                                     team = table$Team,
                                     reduction = table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP01)`)

averted_age <- data.frame(scenario = scenario,
                         team = ages$team,
                         agegroup = ages$Agegroup,
                         reduction = 100*(ages_1$Cml - ages$Cml) / ages_1$Cml )

HP09

VX1 & SC1 & AV

  • “Early”: Vaccine available 100 days after September 1
  • Weekly Symptomatic Prevalence > 1% trigger, early (VX1) vaccine availability reopening
  • Antivirals
scenario <- "HP09_"

long <- read_overall_mean(scn = scenario)

ggplot(data = long, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("% Incident Symptomatic Illness") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cumulative % Ill` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Absolute Averted % Ill (HP01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cumulative % Ill` - table$`Cumulative % Ill`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cumulative % Ill` - table$`Cumulative % Ill`) / table1$`Cumulative % Ill`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "HP09: Compared to HP01", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))
